# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# Smart Monitor v3.0 — Environment Configuration
# Copy to .env and fill in your values:
#   sudo cp .env.example /opt/smart_monitor/.env
#   sudo nano /opt/smart_monitor/.env
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ── Server Identity ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# YOUR custom name for this server.
# This appears in EVERY alert email subject and JSON log record so you
# can instantly tell which server fired the alert when you have multiple
# servers running this monitor.
#
# Examples:
#   SERVER_NAME=prod-web-01
#   SERVER_NAME=db-server-mumbai
#   SERVER_NAME=bastion-host-us-east
#
# If you leave this blank, the OS hostname is used automatically.
SERVER_NAME=

# ── Email Alerts (AWS SES) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set MAIL_ENABLED=false to skip email and only write to the JSON log.
MAIL_ENABLED=true

AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
AWS_REGION=ap-south-1

# Who sends the alert email
SES_SENDER_EMAIL=alerts@your-domain.com

# Who receives it (comma-separated for multiple)
SES_RECIPIENT_EMAILS=admin@your-domain.com

# ── Alert JSON Log Path ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# All alerts are written here regardless of MAIL_ENABLED.
# File is chmod 600 root:root — only root can read it.
ALERT_JSON_PATH=/var/log/smart_monitor_alerts.json
